<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Barbary" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Barbary,</orth> 1) the northwestern part of Africa: <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.272" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 272</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 84</bibl>. <cit><quote>a B. cockpigeon,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.151" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 151</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a B. hen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 108</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a B. horse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 155</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 155</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 112</bibl>.<lb />2) == Barbary horse: <cit><quote>rode on roan B.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.78" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 78</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>rode he on B.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.78" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 V, 5, 78</bibl></cit>
